This repository implements Power Ledger: a Linux power/event accounting daemon and CLI.

The detailed task prompts live in `.cursor/power_ledger_prompts/`.

Do not treat all prompt files as active at once.

Before editing code:
- identify which prompt file controls the current task;
- read `00_master_blueprint.md`;
- read only the specific agent prompt needed for the current task;
- summarize the intended files to create or modify;
- avoid changing unrelated modules.

Implementation rules:
- prefer small C modules with clear headers;
- keep daemon core, D-Bus handling, binary log I/O, IPC socket, CLI, tests, and documentation separated;
- do not invent protocols or binary formats if they are already specified in the prompts;
- add build/test commands whenever code is changed;
- never silently weaken Linux-specific behavior into portable fake behavior.